Grade for Honorary Chief Vivian! \ud83c\udf1f\n\nOn May 28th, our brave and beautiful Honorary Chief Vivian got the ultimate send-off for her last day of 4th grade \u2014 a full law enforcement escort! \ud83d\ude93\ud83d\ude94\ud83d\udc99\n\nAgencies from all across Brevard County, along with our amazing state partners from Florida Highway Patrol, Florida Fish and Wildlife, and the Bureau of Fire, Arson and Explosives, came together to celebrate this incredible young hero.\n\nVivian is courageously fighting DIPG, a rare and aggressive brain tumor, but her strength, smile, and spirit light up every room she enters. \ud83d\udcaa\u2728\n\nShe even brought donuts for the officers (because of course she did \u2014 she\u2019s a true Chief! \ud83c\udf69\ud83d\udc9b), and her little brother got to ride in our Tactical Rescue Vehicle \u2014 a memory he\u2019ll never forget.\n\nTo every agency and officer who stood with us: THANK YOU.
